# MyR Panel — Cursor Rules
# Cursor reads this file automatically on every prompt.
# Never deviate from these rules unless explicitly asked.

## Stack
- React + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS (darkMode: "class")
- i18n via react-i18next — always use t() for user-facing strings
- Routing via react-router-dom
- Auth via useAuth() hook from @shared/auth

## Dark mode
- Dark class is applied to <html> by ThemeProvider
- Always write BOTH light and dark variants: `bg-surface dark:bg-surface-dark`
- Never use bare Tailwind color classes like bg-white, bg-gray-*, text-gray-*, border-gray-*
- Never hardcode hex values in className strings

## Forbidden classes (never use these)
bg-white, bg-gray-50, bg-gray-100, bg-gray-200
text-gray-400, text-gray-500, text-gray-600, text-gray-700, text-gray-900
border-gray-100, border-gray-200, border-gray-300
divide-gray-100, divide-gray-200
hover:bg-gray-50, hover:bg-gray-100

## Color tokens (from tailwind.config.js)
### Backgrounds
- Page background:  bg-background        dark:bg-background-dark       (#F2EFFF / #462671)
- Card/surface:     bg-surface           dark:bg-surface-dark           (#FFFFFF / #603898)
- Input:            bg-surface           dark:bg-white/[0.07]
- Navbar:           bg-navbar            dark:bg-navbar-dark            (#FFFFFF / #1a0a2e)

### Borders
- Default:          border-border        dark:border-border-dark        (#D9C9FF / #8560c0)
- Navbar:           border-navbar-border dark:border-navbar-border-dark (#D9C9FF / #2d1250)
- Input:            border-border        dark:border-input-border-dark

### Text
- Primary:          text-textPrimary     dark:text-textPrimary-dark     (#111827 / #FFFFFF)
- Secondary:        text-textSecondary   dark:text-textSecondary-dark   (#4B5563 / #D4B8FF)

### Brand
- Primary accent:   #E9E8FF  → bg-primary
- Secondary/CTA:    #BF60B5  → bg-secondary   (light mode buttons)
- Pink/CTA dark:    #bf30b5  → bg-pink         (dark mode buttons)
- Table header:     bg-secondary dark:bg-pink  (always white text)

### Status
- Success:  text-status-success  bg-status-success-bg  dark:text-status-success-dark  dark:bg-status-success-dark/15
- Error:    text-status-error    bg-status-error-bg    dark:text-status-error-dark    dark:bg-status-error-dark/15
- Warning:  text-status-warning  bg-status-warning-bg  dark:text-status-warning-dark  dark:bg-status-warning-dark/15

## Utility classes (defined in src/index.css — use these, never reinvent them)
.card             — standard card/panel (surface bg + border + rounded-xl + shadow)
.input            — all form inputs
.btn-primary      — primary CTA button (pink/purple, white text)
.btn-outlined     — secondary button (transparent + border)
.btn-ghost        — tertiary button (no border)
.pag-btn          — pagination buttons
.badge            — base badge (always combine with a modifier)
.badge-success / .badge-error / .badge-warning / .badge-neutral
.alert-error / .alert-warning
.modal-overlay    — fixed fullscreen modal backdrop
.modal-card       — modal content box
.form-label       — label above inputs
.page-root        — outer page wrapper (min-h-screen + bg + transition)
.page-container   — max-width centered content area
.page-header      — flex row: title left, actions right
.page-title       — h1 style
.page-subtitle    — subtitle/description below title
.section-label    — small uppercase section divider
.text-sec         — shorthand for text-textSecondary dark:text-textSecondary-dark
.text-pri         — shorthand for text-textPrimary dark:text-textPrimary-dark

## Table pattern (use this exact structure for every table)
<div className="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-border dark:border-border-dark">
  <table className="min-w-full text-sm">
    <thead className="bg-secondary dark:bg-pink">
      <tr>
        <th className="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-widest whitespace-nowrap">
          Column
        </th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody className="divide-y divide-border dark:divide-border-dark">
      {rows.map((row) => (
        <tr key={row.id} className="hover:bg-secondary/5 dark:hover:bg-white/[0.04] transition-colors duration-150">
          <td className="px-4 py-3 whitespace-nowrap font-medium text-textPrimary dark:text-textPrimary-dark">
            {row.primaryField}
          </td>
          <td className="px-4 py-3 whitespace-nowrap text-textSecondary dark:text-textSecondary-dark">
            {row.secondaryField}
          </td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

## Page pattern (use this exact structure for every new page)
const MyPage = () => {
  return (
    <div className="page-root">
      <div className="page-container">

        {/* Header */}
        <div className="page-header">
          <div>
            <h1 className="page-title">{t('page.title')}</h1>
            <p className="page-subtitle">{t('page.subtitle')}</p>
          </div>
          <div className="flex gap-2">
            <button className="btn-outlined">Secondary action</button>
            <button className="btn-primary">Primary action</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Content */}
        <div className="card p-6">
          ...
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

## Modal pattern
{showModal && (
  <div className="modal-overlay">
    <div className="modal-card max-w-lg">
      <h2 className="text-xl font-bold text-pri mb-4">{t('modal.title')}</h2>
      <p className="text-sec mb-6">{t('modal.body')}</p>
      <div className="flex gap-3">
        <button className="btn-outlined flex-1" onClick={onClose}>Cancel</button>
        <button className="btn-primary flex-1">Confirm</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
)}

## Form pattern
<div className="card p-6 space-y-4">
  <div>
    <label className="form-label">{t('field.label')}</label>
    <input className="input" type="text" placeholder="..." />
  </div>
  <button className="btn-primary w-full">Submit</button>
</div>

## Spacing & shape
- Border radius: rounded-lg (8px) for inputs/buttons, rounded-xl (12px) for cards/modals
- Card padding: p-6 (standard), p-8 (large/hero sections)
- Page vertical padding: py-10
- Gap between stacked cards: space-y-6
- Gap between sibling elements: gap-4 (default), gap-2 (tight), gap-6 (loose)

## Shadows
- Cards light:  shadow-card      (subtle purple-tinted)
- Cards dark:   shadow-card-dark (deep black)
- Focus rings:  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(191,96,181,0.18)  — applied via .input:focus in CSS

## Typography
- Page titles:    text-2xl font-bold
- Section titles: text-lg font-semibold
- Body:           text-sm
- Labels/meta:    text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide
- Monospace IDs:  font-mono text-sm

## Transitions
- Theme toggle:   transition-colors duration-300 (on page root)
- Hover effects:  transition-all duration-200 (on interactive elements)
- Buttons:        hover:-translate-y-px (subtle lift)

## What NOT to do
- Never wrap everything in one giant card — page header floats, table has its own card
- Never use inline styles for colors — use tokens
- Never use purple-*, indigo-* Tailwind palette classes
- Never skip dark: variant on any color class
- Never create a new component if a utility class already covers it
- Never use <form> tags — use div + onClick handlers
- Never add margins to .card itself — control spacing from the parent
